<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   Good as Gold
</HL>
<DATE>
08/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<IN>
PRECIOUS METALS, STONES, GOLD, SILVER (PCS)
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
FOREIGN-EXCHANGE MARKETS (FRX)
</IN>
<LP>
   Robert L. Bartley's July 10 editorial-page article, "The
Great International Growth Slowdown," is brilliant. As one
option to establishing international monetary order, a return
to the gold standard seems sensible. In a follow-up article,
could you please expand upon the pros and cons of gold's
ability to bring back an era of international economic growth
-- which as a byproduct should contribute greatly to world
peace, a higher standard of living and a higher quality of
life for five billion people.
   Irving Lipsiner
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Bethany, Conn.
</TEXT>
