<LP>
   TORONTO -- Robert Hall was named to succeed Robert Jachino
as chief executive officer of Thomson Corp.'s specialized
publishing group, which last year accounted for 39% of
Thomson's $5.11 billion sales and 50.5% of its operating
profit.
   Mr. Jachino, 56 years old, who also is an executive vice
president of Thomson, said in a statement that he planned to
give up his executive positions next Jan. 1, to spend more
time with his family. He will continue as non-executive
chairman of the group, which produces a wide range of
specialized publications in printed and electronic forms.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Thomson said Mr. Hall, 59 years old, also will succeed Mr.
Jachino Jan. 1 as a Thomson director. In the meantime, Mr.
Hall will become chief operating officer of the group Sept.
1. Mr. Hall currently is chief executive officer of Thomson
Financial Services, which publishes financial information.
   Thomson also publishes U.S. and Canadian newspapers and
operates a leisure travel business in Britain.
