<LP>
   SANTA ROSA, Calif. -- A federal bankruptcy court here
dismissd Chapter 11 bankruptcy proceedings filed six months
ago by movie director Francis Ford Coppola and his company
Zoetrope Productions.
   Mr. Coppola, best known for directing the film epic "The
Godfather," had filed for personal and corporate protection
under Chapter 11 in January, seeking protection from creditor
lawsuits while he worked out a plan to pay his debts.
</LP>
