HOME ELECTRONICS, FURNISHINGS, APPLIANCES (HMF)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   PITTSBURGH -- Allegheny International Inc.'s expected
emergence from Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection after 2 1/2
years was delayed at the 11th hour for technical reasons.
   The postponement of the closing -- and a halt in the
company's stock trading on the New York Stock Exchange --
came after the Nuclear Regulatory Commission raised some
questions about the company's Chemetron unit, a shell company
that apparently still retains a nuclear license. The NRC must
approve any transfer of ownership or control when a nuclear
license is involved.
