   The Buttrey division, based in Great Falls, Mont.,
operates 44 food outlets and drugstores in six states, and
has annual sales of $476 million, American said.
   Freeman Spogli, based in Los Angeles, specializes in
management-led buy-outs.
   American Stores, based in Salt Lake City, operates food
stores and drugstores in 37 states.
