<HL>
   REVIEW &amp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:
   Markets Defended
</HL>
<DATE>
08/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A14
</SO>
<CO>
   TAXES
</CO>
<IN>
ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)
</IN>
<LP>
   New York City Comptroller Elizabeth Holtzman, a Democrat,
on the proposed stock-transaction tax: "A bullet aimed at the
heart of New York City. This is a tax on all Americans who
save in the form of stocks and bonds, and in particular, it
is a tax on all American workers' pension funds. This is the
wrong tax at the wrong time." Next thing we know, Governor
Cuomo will be coming out for a cut in the capital-gains tax.
</LP>
<TEXT>
